Package: hhws
Title: Functions for heat-health warning systems
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: c(
	person("Pierre", "Masselot", email = "pierre.masselot@ete.inrs.ca", role = "cre"),
	person("Fateh", "Chebana", email = "fateh.chebana@ete.inrs.ca", role = "aut"))
Description: Functions for finding indicators and thresholds for an heat-health warning system. These functions can be used for systems similar to those currently implemented in France and in the province of Quebec, Canada. It allows computing an over-mortality series, significant over-mortality episodes and find optimal weights and thresholds for the predefined indicators. 
Depends: R (>= 3.5.1)
License: CC0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: forecast (>= 8.4)
RoxygenNote: 6.1.0
